{
  "texts": [
    "The system could account for protected characteristics such as age and ethnicity but has the potential for discrimination.",
    "92 As scholarly literature shows, \"risk analysis largely builds upon gendered and racialized assumptions.\"",
    "93 For instance, the Home Office in the UK has shared that the system detecting potential sham marriages considers, as a risk factor, the age difference between partners.",
    "94 Furthermore, automated systems could be based on methods lacking scientific validity.",
    "In the words of Hildebrandt: \"Reliable AI can only be developed if it is based on a sound and contestable research design anchored in the core tenets of reproducible open science.\""
  ]
}